Huawei recently launched its P30 smartphones, and local operators have now advertised deals for the new devices. The P30 range comprises the P30 and P30 Pro smartphones, along with the mid-range P30 Lite which offers high-end features in a more affordable package. Huaweiâ€™s P30 and P30 Pro offer great new camera features in addition to an overhauled design which minimises the presence of the front camera notch while expanding the edges of the OLED display. Standout features include 50x digital super zoom, reverse wireless charging, on-screen fingerprint biometrics, and AI-powered 7nm processors. The P30 Lite has a less-powerful CPU and camera system. Cash prices currently listed for the devices on Technomobi are as follows: The available contract prices for the Huawei P30 range from MTN and Vodacom are listed below. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-300608" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Huawei-P30-Lite-1.jpg" alt="Huawei P30 Lite 1" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Huawei-P30-Lite-1.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Huawei-P30-Lite-1-300x202.jpg 300w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Huawei-P30-Lite-1-595x400.jpg 595w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-300550" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Huawei-P30-header.jpg" alt="Huawei P30 header" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Huawei-P30-header.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Huawei-P30-header-300x202.jpg 300w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Huawei-P30-header-595x400.jpg 595w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" />